itemDescription: Welsh rugby union and rugby league footballer

wikipedia_page.main: Michael Elliott (born c. 1945) is a Welsh former rugby union, and professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1960s and 1970s who played for Oldham as a three-quarter back. He is an Oldham Hall Of Fame Inductee.
